<note appliesTo="source">line: 2</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: # </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Clock and calendar Add-on for NVDA #</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a96c8e50-7112-4dd4-9e7e-32c82976bc3d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 4</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Authors: Hrvoje Katić, Abdel and NVDA contributors</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c5be4905-76c2-4f80-a110-1aaae154ad38">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 5</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Download [stable version][1]</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c9317aea-190b-47c6-8696-7d5d4b5937b0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 6</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Download [development version][2]</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="233ae1b1-9a72-4ed1-bdc2-0eff571f863c">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 7</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA compatibility: 2019.3 and later</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7de732b2-7642-4f6e-8d1c-0b99dfc54311">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 9</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This add-on enables the advanced clock, alarm timer and calendar functionality for NVDA.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="f1e023d9-9e2e-4593-9ba6-7cc7648b50f2">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 11</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>You can configure NVDA to announce time and date in formats other than what Windows provides by default. Additionally, you can obtain the current day, week number, as well as the remaining days before the end of the current year, and you can also set automatic time announcement on specified interval. There's also a stopwatch and Alarm timer features built-in to the add-on that lets you time your tasks, such as copying files, installing programs, or cooking meals.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="aa4e0a87-e947-4c0a-9f2d-313f978660cd">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 13</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Notes:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="f0d3fc15-e33c-423e-9c38-e383d818ca3a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 15</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>if you install the add-on as an update, during the installation process, the wizard detects if the old configuration is compatible with the new one and offers to correct it before installing, then you'll just have to validate the OK button to confirm that.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="18f747f8-2d1d-49d9-ad0a-00db6bbb4219">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>On Windows 10 and later, you can use Alarms and Clock app to manage stopwatch and timers.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="3bfadf29-2054-4c4a-8c2a-5b6ec6e41b87">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Key commands</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5d666078-51ad-409f-8974-45d736a27b11">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 20</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+F12: get current time</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a12029f8-6ec6-40aa-a321-77d09e7a47f8">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 21</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+F12 pressed twice quickly: get current date</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="70b4f990-95aa-44b4-80b5-bf031983dab5">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+F12 pressed three times quickly: reports the current day, the week number, the current year and the remaining days before the end of the year</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c95059b8-47df-4e4b-ad2a-9e7bd7757ca8">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>NVDA+Shift+F12: enter clock layer</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="0e07c76d-c9fb-4911-bd6d-5b185bf3d9a1">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 25</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Unassigned commands</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="4dd0243d-7301-404b-9230-7bc7563c6599">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 27</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The following commands are not assigned by default; if you wish to assign them, use Input Gestures dialog to add custom commands. To do so, open NVDA menu, Preferences, then Input Gestures. Expand Clock category, then locate unassigned commands from the list below and select "Add", then enter the gesture you wish to use.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="11adf53a-f2ad-484d-aa03-d3ce5f8261fa">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 29</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Elapsed and remaining time before the next alarm. pressing this gesture twice quickly will cancel the next alarm.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="cee593c7-b349-46bb-80e3-5d49f7c48e6d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 30</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Stop currently playing alarm sound.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e965b083-acd2-4991-9ee5-460cead9e9b9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 31</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Display schedule alarms dialog box.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8026efd6-3574-495c-b224-d1e4b6c9d722">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 32</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Show layered commands (keys to be pressed after NVDA+Shift+F12).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="04d27086-9555-4ff1-95d0-b308dd5e659a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 34</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Layered commands</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c4d07530-85b4-4c6f-9276-93d3d6e5d29e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 36</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>To use layered commands, press NVDA+Shift+F12 followed by one of the following keys:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6df8922d-7a96-4679-8599-95aab54170c0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 38</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>S: Starts, resets or stops the stopwatch</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c28116a2-9571-4e0f-82fe-2d46826d4266">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 39</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>R: Resets stopwatch to 0 without restarting it</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="135aae3c-52d5-4f96-a389-9b772386a8d9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 40</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>A: gives the elapsed and remaining time before the next alarm</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="0be9cdb7-aea1-4845-aeb6-4826c8f5ba7e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 41</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>T: opens schedule alarms dialog.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="0de04017-0997-4f41-8dec-ece237146b17">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 42</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>C: Cancel the next alarm</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="204fda6a-28f0-4305-b758-ecfe698ea12a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 43</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Space: Speaks current stopwatch or count-down timer</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1a79fbe0-1f1c-4e1a-b96f-7ebe86c9e44f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 44</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>p: If an alarm is too long, allows to stop it</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a2aa83f2-9bbd-4d32-ad3d-cbbe31c9d50a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 45</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>H: List all layered commands (Help)</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="69a0048f-e03c-4128-9b57-593068d91445">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 47</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Configuration and usage</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d47d9d07-e8da-4ea7-a8cc-de0fe7ad5184">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 49</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>To configure clock functionality, open NVDA menu, Preferences, then Settings, and configure the following options from Clock panel:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="88778074-80a9-4bfc-8d2e-aab722c2b3dd">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 51</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Time and date display format: use these combo boxes to configure how NVDA will announce time and date when you press NVDA+F12 once or twice quickly, respectively.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d472a991-f729-4e50-8e81-26dfe5e14d27">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 52</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Interval: choose the time announcement interval from this combo box (off, every 10 minutes, 15 minutes, 30 minutes, or every hour).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8239e593-027c-491b-9f35-622ee341f60a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 53</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Time announcement (enabled if interval is not off): choose between speech and sound, sound only, or speech only.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="3196aaba-36c1-431a-84c3-47f71300100a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 54</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Clock chime sound (enabled if interval is not off): Select the default clock chime sound for  intermediate minutes and the top of the hour.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="96a03f2f-eee2-405b-9fb3-ab0fe0f0fc8b">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 55</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Separate hour and intermediate minute chimes (enabled if interval is not off, disabled by default): Enable this checkbox to customize chimes for intermediate minutes separately from the hourly chime.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="bee88bf3-3913-4e27-bbca-1d0d3e6cb6b0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 56</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:   * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Intermediate minutes chime sound (enabled if "Separate hour and intermediate minute chimes" is checked): Select the clock chime sound specifically for intermediate minutes.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="81faa7a9-e2a3-4b54-8f85-90a61ea17413">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 57</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Quiet hours (enabled if interval is not off): select this checkbox to configure quiet hours range when automatic time announcement should not occur.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="f68a43cc-a02e-4fd1-a1b8-27e4bd275a17">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 58</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Quiet hours time format (enabled if quiet hours is enabled): select how quiet hours options are presented (12-hour or 24-hour format).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="432b171c-4433-4561-84e7-ccfb01dee031">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 59</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Quiet hours start and end times: select hour and minute range for quiet hours from hours and minutes combo boxes.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="46c1d9ac-0cd0-4a7e-a3fe-83df8f7ed82d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 61</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>To schedule alarms, open NVDA menu, Tools, then select Schedule Alarms. The dialog contents include:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1772b5ff-8b4d-4c0d-8b58-4ebd96d16bed">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 63</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Alarm duration in: select alarm/timer duration between hours, minutes, and seconds.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="2d2a7eea-5235-4f82-85bc-ac780de978b9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 64</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Duration: enter alarm duration in the unit specified above.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a28462c2-7cdc-43e9-899b-5e4fe662cc79">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 65</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Alarm sound: select the alarm sound to be played.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6ec1f657-aef8-4a8d-a3bc-629fa3492c85">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 66</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Stop and pause buttons: stop or pause a long alarm sound.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ac70785b-55d3-4996-9b4b-222f90c13d5d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 68</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Click OK, and a message will inform you the curretnly selected alarm duration.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
